Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of clustering algorithms for text clustering, which falls under the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also compares different initialization schemes for the KMEANS clustering algorithm, which is a popular machine learning algorithm used in clustering tasks. This makes the paper relevant to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of determinantal point processes, which is a probabilistic model used in machine learning and statistics. This makes the paper relevant to the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), which often involves the use of probabilistic models for natural language processing tasks.
